Dilute the @chicken stock{1%sachet} powder in @water{200%ml}(boiling) (double for 4p).

Trim the @carrot{2}(trimmed), then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into ½ cm thick half-moons.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1}(peeled and chopped) into small pieces.

Chop the @potatoes{1}(chopped into 2cm chunks) (no need to peel).

Cut the @lemon{1} into 4 wedges.

== Almonds ==

Place a #large pan{} over medium heat (no oil).

Dry-fry the @almonds{15%g} until toasted, ~{3-4%minutes}. Remove from the pan and set aside. Remove pan from heat.

== Puree ==

Place a #pot{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Fry the onion until softened, stirring occasionally, ~{4-5%minutes}. Add carrots and potatoes. Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Pour in the stock and cook, covered, over medium heat until fork tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Stir occasionally to prevent sticking.

== Fish ==

Meanwhile, add 2 tbsp @flour{2%tbsp} (double for 4p) to a #plate{} or #bowl{}.

Pat the @hake{250%g} dry with #kitchen paper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw fish.

Dip the hake in the flour to coat evenly on all sides.

Shake off excess flour, season with salt and pepper and set aside.

== Assembly ==

Once the carrot and potatoes are cooked, remove from the heat.

Add a drizzle of oil, the @paprika{1%sachet} and a pinch of salt and pepper to the pot.

Blend to a pureed texture.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to get a smoother consistency.

Return your pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of oil.

Once hot, fry the fish on one side until golden, ~{2-3%minutes}. Turn and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other side.

Once cooked, transfer the hake from the pan and cover to keep warm.

> IMPORTANT: Fish is cooked when opaque in the middle.

Return the pan to medium-low heat (without oil).

Add the @baby spinach{240%g} along with a splash of water. Season with salt and pepper. Cook until wilted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Dish up the carrot and potato puree, placing the fish and wilted spinach on top.

Serve lemon wedges on the side for squeezing over.

Garnish with toasted almonds and a final sprinkling of pepper.